                <pb n="1"/>
            <p>Baltimore Aug. 31<hi rend="sup">st</hi> &#91;1&#93;890<lb/></p>
            <p>Rev Dr S. Morais<lb/>
                My Dear Friend.<lb/></p>
            <p>In my great sorrow I have to address<lb/> you asking you for a kindness.  The congregation<lb/> of my lamented Father D Bettelheim &#91;&#63;&#93; asked<lb/> me to recommend to them a man to deliver a few<lb/> sermons for &#91;Hebrew&#93;.  I know of none.  After much<lb/> thinking I came to the conclusion to mention Dr S.<lb/> Solis Cohen who although a layman is so enthused<lb/> with the holy cause of Israel that he might favor<lb/> the congregation with a few lectures.  He could thereby<lb/> easily win the congregation for the cause of our Seminary<lb/> as he did with Dr Szold&#39;s congregation.  I wrote to<lb/> Dr Cohen and I write to you to persuade him to accept<lb/> this offer.  Should he refuse please tell me whom<lb/> you would think fit to be recommended as I am<lb/> afraid the Cincin. College might be asked &#91;Hebrew&#93;<lb/> &#91;Hebrew&#93;.  I leave for New York in an hour and hope<lb/> to receive favorable answer by tomorrow or so<lb/> God bless you&#33;  Yours sorrowfully A Kohut<lb/></p>
            </body>
    </text>
